node.text:
I have spoken a few times on my wall about what a privilege it is to have sponsors, and how reaching an agreement is so much more than just a ‘contract’. It’s about what works for the horses first, the shared values between myself the brand, and discovering more about the teams behind the company.

Below is a lovely example of this and how nice it can be when you really get to know the people behind the brands, they are horse loving people just like us! 

So today my face lit up when I received this. This is 6 years old, Eve Grace Moody,  who I first met when her mum and dad (owners of @bloomfieldshorseboxes , who I have just partnered with) came to the stables for the box handover and on learning, she is a keen rider, I let her sit on Valegro who obviously took very good care of her 🙏🏻 

Today she begged her mum to send this video to me as it was her first ever time off the lead rein, with her beautiful pony Flo. She said to her mum, Helen, that she must show her the WhatsApp to prove that she had sent the video to me😂☺️ 

Well Eve, I am very proud of you; you have done really well today and I am looking forward to seeing your riding progress.

So yes, sponsorship is of course still a huge privilege for me, and still something I am so grateful for....but even more so, when it brings about such lovely messages and moments like these x

🎧 on until the end ☺️☺️☺️☺️

🌟🌟Driving Force - Sky Sports🌟🌟

The episode of ‘Driving Force’ featuring myself and Judy Murray is on air tomorrow night at 9pm GMT
Channel: Sky Sports Mix 
First Airing 28th December

Driving Force
Judy Murray interviews the biggest names in sport and explore stories of success, discrimination and achieving the impossible for a new Sky Sports docuseries 'Driving Force'.

The series, which started on November 24, is exclusive to Sky Sports and explores the making of athletes and the driving forces behind their success.

It aims to shine a light on inequality and other challenges in sport and has a view to calling out, educating and highlighting the need for change for future generations. Across the series, athletes lay their stories bare and unveil both the negative and positive sides of professional sport.

Hope you are able to watch and thank you to Sky for this opportunity 🙏🏻

@pow.tv_ @drivingforceseries

node.text:
What a Championships and what an incredible few months. How do I keep putting this into words!! 

I am so proud of this horse; so green, so inexperienced, but he just gives so much to please and understand what is asked of him. Whatever the outcome, whatever the result, this and only this, is all that matters. Thank you to my team mates, @carlhestermbe @hughesdressage1 and @lottie_fry ; you made this such a fun week and I am proud to be on a team with you!! Silver team medal 🥈 wow. Ian Cast, (@casty300 )thank you for being a rock to all. 

Alan, Lucy; the horses looked amazing and beautifully turned out as always. These medals are yours also 🙏🏻

@renaihart our boy is ❤️❤️❤️❤️

To the wider support team, federations; we know how lucky we are to have such support and organisation. Thank you for being by our side this week. To my sponsors; I am forever grateful and proud to represent your brands so thank you for the kind messages.

Pumpkins bronze medal in the Freestyle was overwhelming last night, in the stunning surrounding of Hof Kasslemans showground. Congratulations to @jessica_von_bredow_werndl on your 🥇 and @cathrinedufour for the 🥈 

A brilliant show and so many memories made, here in Hagen. A well earned break for the horses now. 🙏🏻 thank you to you all of you on here for the support; you words and comments drive us forward xx

#hagenatw2021 #feieuros2021

node.text:
Another brilliant ‘Evening With” for Carl and I last week at Cheltenham Racecourse. Thank you to all of you who came to the event, to hear us talk about all things Tokyo; our horses and why I am not looking forward to Carl’s Christmas video ideas this year 🤣😉 @garethgjenkins you are a super interviewer and @boswell_henry and @harrisonashton1 the funniest roving hosts! I enjoyed every minute of it. 

Thank you to my team for hosting the evening again and to @nafuk for supporting the event. Also to @jennypackham , my- go- to designer, for the beautiful dress and @suziegee.mua for the glow up 😉

Those of you who saw Good Morning Britain know that my mum has been very ill of late, so her being there with my family completed the night ❤️

All pictures by our photographer @jesstog will be available early next week, so I’ll pop a link of here when it’s ready. But for now, we look forward to the European Championships. I’ll keep you posted x

node.text:
So Carl and I had a chat this morning about the 'Evening With' event and quite honestly, we have been truly overwhelmed with the reaction to it, and reading that this is a type of event you would like to go to. 

You can say that's hard to believe, but trust me, it's one thing competing, but having people excited to hear us talk about our careers, Tokyo and beyond....mind...blown.

Tuesday really was an amazing night, so after going through our schedule today, we have decided that in TWO WEEKS time, we are doing it AGAIN. Bigger venue, another interview, another celebration! So excited!!!

CHELTENHAM RACECOURSE: we are coming for you!!
